Get your ass back home!

293
00:14:14,779 --> 00:14:16,279
How much can your paintings even earn?

294
00:14:16,559 --> 00:14:17,799
Your wife's about to give birth!

295
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:18,919
Doing this junk is pointless!

296
00:14:18,919 --> 00:14:19,759
Teacher! Teacher! Teacher!

297
00:14:20,000 --> 00:14:20,539
Teacher, I'm sorry.

298
00:14:20,899 --> 00:14:21,299
Um...

299
00:14:22,940 --> 00:14:23,600
Sorry about this.

300
00:14:25,200 --> 00:14:25,940
Just teach me first.

301
00:14:26,279 --> 00:14:27,539
I'll pay you back later.

302
00:14:29,179 --> 00:14:29,720
Young man,

303
00:14:30,360 --> 00:14:31,259
that's not allowed.

304
00:14:31,720 --> 00:14:32,539
We have rules here.

305
00:14:32,799 --> 00:14:33,139
No, wait,

306
00:14:34,240 --> 00:14:34,539
Teacher,

307
00:14:34,539 --> 00:14:36,120
didn't you say it yourself earlier?

308
00:14:36,720 --> 00:14:38,600
Art can't be measured by money.

309
00:14:38,980 --> 00:14:39,600
Just this once,

310
00:14:39,779 --> 00:14:40,720
break through

311
00:14:40,860 --> 00:14:42,279
the chains of money and rules.

312
00:14:42,639 --> 00:14:43,679
Just teach me first, okay?

313
00:14:45,480 --> 00:14:46,779
Art comes from life,

314
00:14:47,460 --> 00:14:49,620
but life is built on money.

315
00:14:50,200 --> 00:14:51,179
If you want to make art,

316
00:14:52,440 --> 00:14:53,500
you have to survive first.

317
00:15:07,080 --> 00:15:09,059
I told you to go win your wife back,

318
00:15:09,419 --> 00:15:10,419
and you ran off to paint?

319
00:15:10,659 --> 00:15:12,039
You're deliberately messing with me, huh?

320
00:15:13,320 --> 00:15:13,940
From this day on,

321
00:15:14,519 --> 00:15:16,019
don't expect a single cent from this house.

322
00:15:17,539 --> 00:15:18,360
You, and you too!

323
00:15:19,200 --> 00:15:21,120
If you dare sneak him money again,

324
00:15:21,340 --> 00:15:22,799
I'll kick you out along with him!

325
00:15:25,240 --> 00:15:25,620
You stay right here

326
00:15:25,620 --> 00:15:26,259
and behave yourself.

327
00:15:26,759 --> 00:15:27,679
Tomorrow you're coming to sell goods with me.

328
00:15:28,779 --> 00:15:29,500
I'm not going.

329
00:15:31,580 --> 00:15:32,200
Not going, huh?

330
00:15:32,960 --> 00:15:34,019
Then don't expect to eat!

331
00:15:35,100 --> 00:15:35,399
You...

332
00:15:36,940 --> 00:15:38,039
Not even allowed to eat?

333
00:15:38,059 --> 00:15:39,000
I'll starve to death!

334
00:15:39,399 --> 00:15:40,659
No work, no food!

335
00:15:41,419 --> 00:15:42,600
I don't feed freeloaders here.

336
00:15:44,480 --> 00:15:45,120
I'm telling you,

337
00:15:45,820 --> 00:15:46,600
don't give him any food!

338
00:15:46,740 --> 00:15:47,580
Let him starve for a bit!

339
00:15:48,840 --> 00:15:50,419
Spare the rod, spoil the child.

340
00:16:13,179 --> 00:16:14,259
Where'd you get the key?

341
00:16:15,899 --> 00:16:17,159
I made a copy ages ago.

342
00:16:20,820 --> 00:16:21,220
Son.

343
00:16:21,779 --> 00:16:22,679
Mom's got your back.

344
00:16:25,440 --> 00:16:26,799
Look at these hands of yours.

345
00:16:28,220 --> 00:16:29,620
Those are a painter's hands.

346
00:16:30,879 --> 00:16:32,519
Don't let your dad hold you back.

347
00:16:33,220 --> 00:16:34,340
Pack your things.

348
00:16:35,179 --> 00:16:35,879
You're going to Shenzhen.

349
00:16:37,879 --> 00:16:38,919
I've got no money.

350
00:16:38,980 --> 00:16:40,659
He took all your money too.

351
00:16:42,899 --> 00:16:44,159
I've been battling him my whole life.

352
00:16:44,480 --> 00:16:46,100
Think I'd let him clean me out?

353
00:16:57,580 --> 00:16:58,600
Mom's gotta go dig it up.

354
00:17:00,879 --> 00:17:02,259
You didn't forget, did you?

355
00:17:02,740 --> 00:17:03,259
No way.

356
00:17:38,279 --> 00:17:38,599
This...

357
00:18:01,799 --> 00:18:03,240
Old Qi

358
00:18:04,200 --> 00:18:05,380
Where's my money?

359
00:18:07,619 --> 00:18:09,160
You wanna mess with me?

360
00:18:11,299 --> 00:18:12,720
I've cleaned out

361
00:18:13,400 --> 00:18:14,380
your whole stash.

362
00:19:04,299 --> 00:19:04,599
Right.

363
00:19:04,759 --> 00:19:06,259
We're raising the money right now.

364
00:19:06,539 --> 00:19:07,660
And if all goes well,

365
00:19:07,660 --> 00:19:09,039
we'll probably come after Mid-Autumn

366
00:19:09,039 --> 00:19:10,039
to sign the contract with you.

367
00:19:10,700 --> 00:19:11,519
Great, great.

368
00:19:11,819 --> 00:19:12,579
See you after the holiday.

369
00:19:12,740 --> 00:19:13,240
Thank you, boss.

370
00:19:15,920 --> 00:19:17,220
All right, come on.

371
00:19:17,339 --> 00:19:18,440
High five!

372
00:19:18,500 --> 00:19:20,160
Almost there. Just need the money.

373
00:19:20,559 --> 00:19:21,599
Just the money.

374
00:19:21,599 --> 00:19:22,680
Money's the hardest part.

375
00:19:22,680 --> 00:19:23,380
You know?

376
00:19:23,740 --> 00:19:24,640
Right now, I can't even borrow

377
00:19:24,660 --> 00:19:26,220
enough to pay for Grandma's treatment.

378
00:19:26,220 --> 00:19:27,019
Let alone this.

379
00:19:27,880 --> 00:19:28,680
Before,

380
00:19:28,680 --> 00:19:29,900
I did save up twenty thousand yuan.

381
00:19:30,240 --> 00:19:31,700
But it all went to Grandma's medical bills.

382
00:19:32,940 --> 00:19:33,779
You've got the skills.

383
00:19:33,940 --> 00:19:34,680
You can do a Technology Investment.

384
00:19:34,940 --> 00:19:35,319
No money needed.

385
00:19:35,720 --> 00:19:36,440
How much short are we?

386
00:19:37,079 --> 00:19:37,619
I've got money.

387
00:19:39,539 --> 00:19:40,480
How much do you have?

388
00:19:40,920 --> 00:19:41,940
Every year's Lucky money,

389
00:19:41,940 --> 00:19:42,940
I secretly saved it all up.

390
00:19:43,200 --> 00:19:44,119
It's quite a bit.

391
00:19:44,759 --> 00:19:46,500
Lucky money?

392
00:19:46,500 --> 00:19:48,359
At least one or two thousand, right?

393
00:19:48,359 --> 00:19:48,980
Two or three thousand?

394
00:19:49,200 --> 00:19:49,579
What?

395
00:19:49,940 --> 00:19:50,619
One or two thousand?

396
00:19:51,339 --> 00:19:51,720
Jingjing,

397
00:19:51,720 --> 00:19:53,140
you really underestimate me.

398
00:19:54,140 --> 00:19:54,859
Monopoly!

399
00:19:55,519 --> 00:19:55,819
I'm...

400
00:19:55,940 --> 00:19:57,799
back when Old Qian hadn't gone broke yet.

401
00:19:58,759 --> 00:19:59,339
You scared me!

402
00:19:59,400 --> 00:19:59,920
Dandan,

403
00:20:00,220 --> 00:20:01,140
why are you here?

404
00:20:01,380 --> 00:20:02,400
Your mom's been looking everywhere for you.

405
00:20:02,500 --> 00:20:02,880
Hurry, go.

406
00:20:02,920 --> 00:20:04,400
Why didn't you knock before coming in?

407
00:20:05,319 --> 00:20:05,720
I...

408
00:20:06,539 --> 00:20:07,500
I knew you'd be staying here

409
00:20:07,500 --> 00:20:08,500
with Xiaofang tonight.

410
00:20:08,980 --> 00:20:09,599
Afraid you'd get cold,

411
00:20:09,599 --> 00:20:10,960
so I brought you a quilt.

412
00:20:11,440 --> 00:20:12,839
You still have to knock!

413
00:20:13,059 --> 00:20:14,119
Everyone's got privacy.

414
00:20:14,119 --> 00:20:14,700
Okay?

415
00:20:15,039 --> 00:20:15,940
I'm your mother.

416
00:20:16,500 --> 00:20:18,200
Why do you always

417
00:20:18,200 --> 00:20:19,599
find fault with everything I do?

418
00:20:19,920 --> 00:20:21,339
If you have any issue with me,

419
00:20:21,339 --> 00:20:22,799
can't we just talk it out nicely?

420
00:20:23,779 --> 00:20:24,319
You remember this.

421
00:20:24,859 --> 00:20:26,279
Everything I've ever done in my life

422
00:20:26,339 --> 00:20:27,259
comes down to three words:

423
00:20:27,819 --> 00:20:28,460
It's for your own good.

424
00:20:32,819 --> 00:20:33,700
Enough, enough, enough.

425
00:20:33,779 --> 00:20:34,680
I don't want to fight today.

426
00:20:34,720 --> 00:20:35,319
Don't talk to me.

427
00:20:51,819 --> 00:20:52,799
You can't just spend your whole life

428
00:20:52,819 --> 00:20:53,980
not talking to your mom.

429
00:20:54,859 --> 00:20:56,319
"It's for your own good, for your own good."

430
00:20:56,759 --> 00:20:58,059
All day long, "It's for your own good."

431
00:20:58,619 --> 00:20:59,299
Does she even know

432
00:20:59,299 --> 00:21:00,279
what's really good for me?

433
00:21:00,980 --> 00:21:02,599
Those words just set me off.

434
00:21:03,759 --> 00:21:06,059
I wish my mom were that civilized.

435
00:21:06,920 --> 00:21:08,660
The moment she says "for your own good,"

436
00:21:08,660 --> 00:21:09,240
those very words,

437
00:21:09,839 --> 00:21:11,220
she's definitely about to hit me.

438
00:21:11,700 --> 00:21:12,720
Beating me is "for my own good."

439
00:21:13,200 --> 00:21:14,259
Well, thanks a lot, Mom.

440
00:21:15,880 --> 00:21:17,000
Poor Dandan.

441
00:21:17,000 --> 00:21:18,000
Just bear with it.

442
00:21:18,500 --> 00:21:19,400
Can't beat her,

443
00:21:19,640 --> 00:21:20,660
but we can always dodge her.

444
00:21:20,839 --> 00:21:21,259
Right?

445
00:21:21,960 --> 00:21:23,200
You can't bear it,

446
00:21:23,480 --> 00:21:24,740
and Dandan, you can't dodge her either.

447
00:21:25,880 --> 00:21:27,380
It all boils down to one phrase:

448
00:21:27,839 --> 00:21:28,380
"It's for your own good."

449
00:21:28,779 --> 00:21:29,799
They really do believe

450
00:21:29,799 --> 00:21:30,579
it's for our own good.

451
00:21:31,359 --> 00:21:32,319
But their methods,

452
00:21:32,319 --> 00:21:33,160
we just can't stand.

453
00:21:34,039 --> 00:21:34,619
Let's work hard.

454
00:21:34,759 --> 00:21:36,299
Work hard to prove we don't need

455
00:21:36,299 --> 00:21:37,339
them looking out for us.

456
00:21:38,980 --> 00:21:40,319
The nail salon is now our chance

457
00:21:40,319 --> 00:21:41,079
to prove ourselves.

458
00:21:41,619 --> 00:21:42,619
But right now, we can't even

459
00:21:42,619 --> 00:21:43,480
scrape the money together.

460
00:21:44,740 --> 00:21:45,740
We can find outside help.

461
00:21:49,279 --> 00:21:49,839
Like who?

462
00:21:51,720 --> 00:21:53,220
Take them down one by one.

463
00:21:53,799 --> 00:21:55,180
How's it going, bro?

464
00:21:56,660 --> 00:21:57,559
What can I say?

465
00:21:57,880 --> 00:21:58,880
Just figuring out my next move.

466
00:21:59,480 --> 00:22:00,380
Come back after the holiday.

467
00:22:00,980 --> 00:22:01,880
I'll plead your case again.

468
00:22:03,119 --> 00:22:03,480
Forget it.

469
00:22:04,180 --> 00:22:04,680
It's pointless.

470
00:22:05,440 --> 00:22:06,420
Stop toughing it out.

471
00:22:07,039 --> 00:22:08,480
Time to bow down to reality.

472
00:22:10,059 --> 00:22:10,960
Bow down?

473
00:22:11,559 --> 00:22:13,019
I've been bowing all along. It's useless.

474
00:22:13,940 --> 00:22:14,779
Let me think it over.

475
00:22:15,059 --> 00:22:15,519
I'm hanging up.

476
00:22:18,720 --> 00:22:20,119
If I can win 500 today,

477
00:22:23,180 --> 00:22:23,660
from two packs!

478
00:22:25,480 --> 00:22:26,519
if I can win 500,

479
00:22:26,680 --> 00:22:27,740
I'll pick myself up

480
00:22:27,740 --> 00:22:28,339
and get back in the game.

481
00:22:34,160 --> 00:22:35,200
Neither ticket won a thing.

482
00:22:35,779 --> 00:22:36,220
I swear...

483
00:22:36,859 --> 00:22:37,500
What a piece of junk.

484
00:22:38,339 --> 00:22:39,440
So annoying, day after day.

485
00:22:40,460 --> 00:22:41,319
I can't believe myself.

486
00:22:41,460 --> 00:22:42,359
I'm so fed up.

487
00:22:44,880 --> 00:22:47,279
Nice weather, isn't it? Yeah.

488
00:22:47,500 --> 00:22:48,140
Uncle.

489
00:22:48,160 --> 00:22:48,799
Uncle.

490
00:22:49,579 --> 00:22:51,420
The weather's really nice today.

491
00:22:51,660 --> 00:22:52,759
Really.

492
00:22:53,180 --> 00:22:53,839
Where have you two been?

493
00:22:54,200 --> 00:22:55,119
And you're alone here again,

494
00:22:55,119 --> 00:22:56,319
pondering life?

495
00:22:57,079 --> 00:22:58,019
I came to wash some veggies.

496
00:22:58,019 --> 00:22:58,980
Aren't we eating soon?

497
00:22:59,000 --> 00:23:00,940
I'm doing prenatal yoga.

498
00:23:09,039 --> 00:23:09,819
Jingjing

499
00:23:10,140 --> 00:23:10,900
I really think

500
00:23:10,900 --> 00:23:12,859
we're incredibly lucky

501
00:23:13,539 --> 00:23:15,619
Such a great nail salon

502
00:23:16,079 --> 00:23:17,059
Been running for two years

503
00:23:17,440 --> 00:23:18,539
with a steady clientele

504
00:23:19,039 --> 00:23:20,559
If the owner weren't in a rush to leave

505
00:23:20,920 --> 00:23:21,980
would we ever get this chance?

506
00:23:22,500 --> 00:23:23,079
Right

507
00:23:23,119 --> 00:23:24,619
We're really lucky

508
00:23:24,640 --> 00:23:26,400
I mean, the beauty industry now

509
00:23:26,420 --> 00:23:27,420
is so profitable

510
00:23:27,880 --> 00:23:29,019
Something like nails

511
00:23:29,059 --> 00:23:30,819
as long as your taste and skills are on point

512
00:23:31,000 --> 00:23:32,640
you're guaranteed to make money

513
00:23:32,640 --> 00:23:33,019
Right?

514
00:23:33,460 --> 00:23:34,559
Exactly

515
00:23:35,200 --> 00:23:36,559
Oh, and I just remembered

516
00:23:36,859 --> 00:23:38,200
Did I ever tell you

517
00:23:38,359 --> 00:23:39,700
I learned latte art

518
00:23:39,880 --> 00:23:40,660
So down the line

519
00:23:41,079 --> 00:23:43,319
let's add another feature to the shop

520
00:23:43,779 --> 00:23:44,339
You

521
00:23:44,579 --> 00:23:45,779
handle the nails on one side

522
00:23:46,140 --> 00:23:48,720
and I'll make coffee on the other

523
00:23:49,000 --> 00:23:49,759
and milk tea

524
00:23:50,180 --> 00:23:52,000
Another stream of income

525
00:23:52,559 --> 00:23:54,859
That's a brilliant idea

526
00:23:56,700 --> 00:23:58,220
Doing this

527
00:23:58,380 --> 00:24:00,799
beats all that flashy nonsense

528
00:24:00,859 --> 00:24:02,140
by a mile, way more reliable

529
00:24:02,200 --> 00:24:02,619
Right?

530
00:24:02,779 --> 00:24:04,579
Exactly

531
00:24:04,579 --> 00:24:06,460
You two say this nail salon

532
00:24:06,940 --> 00:24:07,680
has real potential?

533
00:24:11,359 --> 00:24:12,460
Uncle

534
00:24:13,420 --> 00:24:14,779
Do you want

535
00:24:15,240 --> 00:24:16,460
to buy in too?

536
00:24:19,380 --> 00:24:20,119
Let me think about it

537
00:24:22,339 --> 00:24:23,200
Let me observe first

538
00:24:53,819 --> 00:24:55,359
In the age of big data,

539
00:24:56,599 --> 00:24:58,240
gathering customer information

540
00:24:58,500 --> 00:25:00,720
is key to expanding your clientele.

541
00:25:00,859 --> 00:25:02,359
And this top-of-the-line

542
00:25:02,519 --> 00:25:03,200
laptop computer,

543
00:25:03,559 --> 00:25:04,319
do you have one?

544
00:25:04,819 --> 00:25:05,539
This is an old model, isn't it?

545
00:25:05,619 --> 00:25:06,779
You don't have one.

546
00:25:07,579 --> 00:25:08,259
High-end speakers,

547
00:25:09,059 --> 00:25:09,500
do you have any?

548
00:25:10,759 --> 00:25:11,920
These are a bit old.

549
00:25:11,920 --> 00:25:12,880
You don't have them.

550
00:25:13,259 --> 00:25:15,240
While clients get their nails done,

551
00:25:15,319 --> 00:25:16,660
top-tier speakers

552
00:25:16,660 --> 00:25:18,079
play the coziest music,

553
00:25:18,599 --> 00:25:19,420
instantly elevating

554
00:25:19,579 --> 00:25:21,660
an ordinary street-side nail salon

555
00:25:21,859 --> 00:25:23,400
to a whole new level.

556
00:25:24,940 --> 00:25:25,779
And this,

557
00:25:31,819 --> 00:25:32,579
a gaming console.

558
00:25:33,319 --> 00:25:33,660
Uncle,

559
00:25:33,660 --> 00:25:34,980
why didn't you bring this out sooner?

560
00:25:35,539 --> 00:25:35,940
Look.

561
00:25:37,200 --> 00:25:37,640
Look.

562
00:25:38,359 --> 00:25:40,059
The kid can happily settle down

563
00:25:40,059 --> 00:25:41,039
and play games here,

564
00:25:41,259 --> 00:25:41,940
while I

565
00:25:42,279 --> 00:25:44,200
can peacefully get my nails done.

566
00:25:44,960 --> 00:25:45,720
So, Uncle,

567
00:25:48,279 --> 00:25:49,059
you're planning

568
00:25:49,059 --> 00:25:50,240
to use this stuff

569
00:25:50,920 --> 00:25:51,519
as your investment?

570
00:25:52,099 --> 00:25:52,920
Just this?

571
00:25:53,779 --> 00:25:54,579
How shallow.

572
00:25:56,500 --> 00:25:58,339
What I value is this team.

573
00:25:58,960 --> 00:25:59,539
Xiaofang

574
00:26:00,420 --> 00:26:01,819
has the boldest spirit among us.

575
00:26:02,220 --> 00:26:03,240
And our Jingjing

576
00:26:03,839 --> 00:26:04,779
has top-notch skills.

577
00:26:05,359 --> 00:26:07,000
Her nail work is beyond words.

578
00:26:07,299 --> 00:26:08,099
And I

579
00:26:08,720 --> 00:26:10,980
am the indispensable brains,

580
00:26:11,839 --> 00:26:12,960
the wisdom of the team,

581
00:26:13,779 --> 00:26:15,099
the creative director.

582
00:26:15,819 --> 00:26:16,460
What about me?

583
00:26:18,400 --> 00:26:19,240
You've got to be here too.

584
00:26:19,839 --> 00:26:21,160
We'll test the nails on you.

585
00:26:21,200 --> 00:26:21,680
Our little guinea pig.

586
00:26:23,500 --> 00:26:25,579
