634
00:28:12,440 --> 00:28:12,880
Twelve.

635
00:28:13,279 --> 00:28:14,099
But no more than that.

636
00:28:15,900 --> 00:28:17,140
Okay, okay, deal.

637
00:28:17,140 --> 00:28:18,380
I've got a bit of money saved up.

638
00:28:18,759 --> 00:28:19,700
How about I give it all to you?

639
00:28:19,759 --> 00:28:20,539
Sure, wire it to my card.

640
00:28:20,559 --> 00:28:21,079
I'll take all of it.

641
00:28:21,140 --> 00:28:22,440
All of it, all of it.

642
00:28:22,480 --> 00:28:23,519
He really doesn't mind taking it all.

643
00:28:23,539 --> 00:28:24,779
Really, more is always better.

644
00:28:25,039 --> 00:28:26,079
Are you really my dad?

645
00:28:26,759 --> 00:28:28,019
Are you really my uncle?

646
00:28:28,099 --> 00:28:29,279
Are you really my dear uncle?

647
00:28:34,880 --> 00:28:37,440
Talk about asking for the moon!

648
00:29:58,700 --> 00:30:00,839
In books, one can find houses of gold.

649
00:30:01,700 --> 00:30:02,240
Nail salon

650
00:30:04,480 --> 00:30:05,079
Secret stash

651
00:30:06,380 --> 00:30:07,000
Nail salon

652
00:30:08,019 --> 00:30:09,359
Secret stash

653
00:30:11,819 --> 00:30:14,619
How should we split this?

654
00:30:18,440 --> 00:30:20,200
Just give it all to me.

655
00:30:20,839 --> 00:30:21,440
Give it back!

656
00:30:21,759 --> 00:30:23,099
Give it back! Give it back! Mine!

657
00:30:23,140 --> 00:30:23,880
Let go!

658
00:30:26,680 --> 00:30:28,519
Where'd you get all this money?

659
00:30:28,579 --> 00:30:29,420
It's my money.

660
